{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:27:35.194Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Preview Sections**\n\nI'm structuring the preview page with clearly defined sections. I'm focusing on aligning these with the eleven necessary sections. Currently, I'm identifying and listing the core elements, starting with an Executive Summary, Challenge Statement, and a Recommended GFF Path.\n\n\n**Updating Section Parameters**\n\nI'm now focused on the function `generateProposalData()`. I need to ensure it provides all the required parameters for dynamic section building. I've begun to define the initial components: Executive Summary, Challenge Statement, and the Recommended GFF Path. I am aiming for a highly deterministic output.\n\n\n**Addressing System Risks**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the inherent risks of party AI systems. SaaS telemetry and siloed data present real operational latency. This threatens performance and introduces vulnerabilities, potentially leading to increased costs. I'm focusing on the GFF Path section specifically, and its crucial elements, and how to improve security.\n\n\n**Detailing Future Project Tasks**\n\nI am now structuring detailed tasks for the project roadmap. I'm focusing on the technical workstreams: Hardened read-only connectors and token dispatch for OmniMesh, custom multi-agent consensus workflows and safety checks, and real-time compliance ledger with sandbox handoff. I'm building out a clear 90-day integration plan with 30-day sprints. The roadmap includes isolation, proof-of-concept, and agent workflow implementation.\n\n\n**Defining Governance Requirements**\n\nI'm now outlining a governance approach for the project, focusing on a \"Zero Trust, Zero Retention\" framework. I've broken it down into access boundaries, and the importance of data privacy. Specifically, I'm defining the squad structure needed to meet the targets for `{org}`, including roles for lead AI architect, systems engineers, and a security/compliance auditor. I'm thinking about how their roles will provide clear guidelines, and the importance of zero persistent retention.\n\n\n**Defining Security Safeguards**\n\nI'm now detailing critical security safeguards. I'm focusing on ensuring no user prompts or agent context weights are ever cached or sent to external SaaS APIs. Continuous real-time audit logs will track model runs and data mesh transactions. Automated policy watchdogs will block out-of-bounds context before it reaches the execution pipeline, which I view as crucial.\n\nI'm also setting quantified targets to measure the impact of GFF deployment. These include a sub-150ms latency threshold for dynamic cognitive loops, zero external IP leaks or SaaS memory retention logs for intellectual property safety, a 30%+ reclaim of API or third-party license expenses, and 100% automated logging coverage verified by the Sovereign Ledger to maintain compliance. I'm focusing on key assumptions for the project as well, specifically that core data assets and unindexed silos are accessible via read-only VPC network interfaces, and that executive stakeholders will participate in standard meetings.\n\n\n**Outlining Engagement Launch**\n\nI am now structuring the final engagement launch steps. I am focused on the weekly alignment reviews to make sure hardware resources are provisioned on schedule. I have identified the potential barriers and mitigation strategies, including data quality/silo delay, provisioning lead time, and varying regional sovereignty laws. I'm focusing on the plan to start the `{engagementPathObj.label}`, including Dossier signoff and Technical Discovery calls.\n\n\n**Mobilizing Resource Squads**\n\nI'm now focused on the team, provisioning `{engagementPathObj.squad}` resources within seven business days. Also, I'm updating `handleCopyOutline` to create a beautiful markdown format for all eleven sections. This includes the client and industry details.\n\n\n**Refining Document Exports**\n\nI'm now focusing on the export functionality and improving the user interface for document previews. I'm building out a polished display for PPT, PDF, and SOW exports, clearly marking features as \"FUTURE INTEGRATION\" or \"PREMIUM.\" I'm aiming for a sophisticated, enterprise-ready look, with tooltip overlays.\n\n\n"}}
