{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:29:11.558Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"0kuhwp00","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/build/proposal/page.tsx","old_text":"  const handleCopyOutline = () => {\n    const data = generateProposalData();\n    const outlineText = `GFF AI SOVEREIGN INTEGRATION PROPOSAL\n----------------------------------------\nOrganization Name: ${data.org}\nSector Vertical: ${data.industryLabel}\nOperational Footprint: ${data.companySizeLabel}\nGeographic Deployment: ${data.geographyLabel}\nPriority Challenge: ${data.challengeLabel}\nTarget Path: ${data.engagementPathObj.label} (${data.engagementPathObj.badge})\nProject Scope Timeline: ${data.timelineLabel} (${data.weeks} Weeks)\nCore Squad Config: ${data.engagementPathObj.squad}\nCapital Allocation Range: ${data.budgetLabel}\nSponsor Stakeholders: ${data.stakeholdersLabel}\n\nKEY DELIVERABLES:\n${data.deliverables.map((d, i) => `${i + 1}. ${d}`).join(\"\\n\")}\n`;\n    navigator.clipboard.writeText(outlineText);\n    setCopied(true);\n    setTimeout(() => setCopied(false), 2000);\n  };","new_text":"  const handleCopyOutline = () => {\n    const data = generateProposalData();\n    const p1 = data.p1;\n    const p2 = data.p2;\n    const p3 = data.p3;\n    const weeks = data.weeks;\n\n    const outlineText = `GFF AI SOVEREIGN INTEGRATION PROPOSAL & OUTLINE\n======================================================\n[ FRONTEND SANBOX PREVIEW ONLY - NOT A BINDING LEGAL/COMMERCIAL CONTRACT ]\n\nCLIENT: ${data.org}\nVERTICAL: ${data.industryLabel}\nOPERATIONAL SCALE: ${data.companySizeLabel} (${data.companySizeRange})\nVPC DEPLOYMENT REGION: ${data.geographyLabel}\nSELECTED INTAKE BUDGET: ${data.budgetLabel}\nSTAKEHOLDER SPONSORS: ${data.stakeholdersLabel}\n\nPREFERRED ENGAGEMENT PATHWAY: ${data.engagementPathObj.label} (${data.engagementPathObj.badge})\nCALCULATED SOW TIMELINE: ${weeks} Weeks\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION I: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n------------------------------------------------------\nGFF AI recommends deploying a dedicated ${data.engagementPathObj.label} architecture inside the single-tenant VPC perimeter for ${data.org} to address strategic bottlenecks in the ${data.industryLabel} sector. Over an implementation lifecycle of ${weeks} Weeks, GFF will establish isolated secure pipelines under the guidance of key stakeholders (${data.stakeholdersLabel}), delivering sovereign capabilities like ${data.selectedOutcomeLabels.join(\", \")}.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION II: CHALLENGE STATEMENT\n------------------------------------------------------\nFor a ${data.companySizeLabel} enterprise, third-party cloud-hosted AI APIs introduce serious compliance and telemetry leaks. The core technical bottleneck to resolve is \"${data.challengeLabel}\". Left unmitigated, data fragmentation and token cost explosion will slow down operational cycles and expose intellectual property.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION III: RECOMMENDED GFF PATH\n------------------------------------------------------\nPath Recommended: ${data.engagementPathObj.label} (${data.engagementPathObj.badge})\nDeployment Enclave: Single-tenant VPC perimeter within ${data.geographyLabel}.\nThis model ensures absolute data boundaries with strict zero persistent retention logging of query data, completely shielding corporate IP from third-party model caches.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION IV: PROPOSED WORKSTREAMS\n------------------------------------------------------\nThe deployment will proceed across four main workstreams over ${weeks} weeks:\n- Workstream A: Hardened Perimeter Setup (Weeks 1 - ${p1})\n  Configure geographical VPC boundaries, provision isolated secure enclaves, and verify strict zero-retention parameters.\n- Workstream B: Cognitive Pipeline Core Integration (Weeks ${p1 + 1} - ${p1 + p2})\n  Deploy OmniMesh read-only connectors, map structured metadata layers, and configure local semantic indexes.\n- Workstream C: Agent Orchestration & Tuning (Weeks ${p1 + p2 + 1} - ${p1 + p2 + p3})\n  Standardize agent consensus configurations, fine-tune models on local data, and establish workflow guardrails.\n- Workstream D: Telemetry Logging & Sandbox Handoff (Weeks ${p1 + p2 + p3 + 1} - ${weeks})\n  Integrate real-time compliance audit ledgers and operator dashboards, conduct team training, and complete engineering handoff.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION V: 90-DAY ROADMAP\n------------------------------------------------------\nRegardless of the baseline project schedule, GFF operates on a tactical 90-Day Integration Roadmap:\n- Day 1 to 30: Perimeter Isolation & Data Integration\n  Establish core VPC enclaves, link first-stage legacy data sources via OmniMesh read-only boundaries, and validate telemetry.\n- Day 31 to 60: Agent Workflow Design & Customization\n  Orchestrate multi-agent decision nodes, configure feedback loops, and integrate with system actions.\n- Day 61 to 90: Federated Rollout & Sovereign Certification\n  Conduct vulnerability audits, scale cognitive agents across operational teams, and certify against regulatory guidelines.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION VI: SUGGESTED SQUAD\n------------------------------------------------------\nTo ensure perfect execution, GFF suggests deploying the following co-innovation squad:\nSquad Cohort: ${data.engagementPathObj.squad}\n- Lead Solutions Architect: Guides single-tenant topological configurations.\n- Systems Engineers: Programs local weight tuning and memory optimization.\n- Security & Compliance Auditor: Audits the zero persistent retention guardrails.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION VII: GOVERNANCE APPROACH\n------------------------------------------------------\nGFF enforces a \"Zero Trust, Zero Retention\" sovereign AI governance framework:\n- Private single-tenant VPC boundaries strictly partition raw data from external networks.\n- In-memory processing buffers ensure prompts and parameters are immediately zeroed post-inference.\n- Live compliance logging tracks queries on a read-only audit ledger.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION VIII: SUCCESS MEASURES\n------------------------------------------------------\nThe sovereign installation will be measured against these strict criteria:\n- Cognitive Loop Latency: Sub-150ms dynamic decision loop performance.\n- IP Isolation Boundary: 100% trace sanitization with zero retention logging.\n- OpEx Reclamation: 30%+ reclaimed external SaaS token and licensing expenses.\n- Telemetry Auditing: 100% of pipeline transactions logged to the secure audit ledger.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION IX: ASSUMPTIONS\n------------------------------------------------------\nThe project plan assumes:\n- Read-only database access is granted via VPC network boundaries within 7 business days.\n- Stakeholders listed (${data.stakeholdersLabel}) attend brief weekly alignment reviews.\n- Private container sandbox hardware is provisioned according to target specifications.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION X: RISKS & MITIGATIONS\n------------------------------------------------------\n- Risk: High complexity or fragmentation of legacy database silos.\n  Mitigation: GFF OmniMesh constructs real-time semantic context without altering core legacy databases.\n- Risk: Provisioning lead-times on isolated enterprise cloud instances.\n  Mitigation: Simulating agent fleets on local staging enclaves to bypass cloud hardware delays.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nSECTION XI: NEXT STEPS\n------------------------------------------------------\n1. E-Sign and approve this proposal draft below.\n2. Conduct a 1-hour secure VPC configuration and boundary discovery call.\n3. Mobilize the suggested co-innovation squad (${data.engagementPathObj.squad}) within 7 business days.\n\n------------------------------------------------------\nDISCLAIMER & DOCUMENT METRICS\n------------------------------------------------------\n- Document Hash: GFF-SOV-PROPOSAL-${Math.floor(Math.random() * 90000) + 10000}\n- Telemetry Code: 0x4B2FA7\n- Note: Generated locally. This is a frontend demo and not a legally binding contract.\n`;\n    navigator.clipboard.writeText(outlineText);\n    setCopied(true);\n    setTimeout(() => setCopied(false), 2000);\n  };"}}}
