r**\n\nI'm now implementing the compliance ledger visual for Section IV, focusing on a balance of clarity and visual impact. I've designed a zero-retention, secure enclave represented by a stylized, neon-bordered block. I'm leveraging distinct text styling to highlight key attributes like cryptographic logs. This design aims for an expensive and professional aesthetic. I'm also planning four phased blocks representing delivery phases.\n\n\n**Designing the Timeline**\n\nI'm now incorporating a vertical timeline between the ledger blocks. I'll use clean CSS borders to link the delivery phases visually. Next, I'm onto Section V, the 90-day roadmap, which will be a horizontal timeline divided into three sprints, each with a custom label within a grid layout. The goal is clarity and visual appeal.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Boundaries**\n\nI'm now rendering Section VII, focusing on a clean technical matrix for the governance approach. I'll represent the Sovereign Governance Boundary with a custom diagram: `Input Request -> [PII & IP Filter Guard] -> Local In-Memory Inference -> [Trace Sanitization Engine] -> Output Dispatch`. I'm going for a custom and premium feel. Next, I'm working on Section VIII, rendering four data telemetry cards with target values for things like cognitive loop latency. I'll use `ToolDataCard` styling to make them visually appealing.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Proposal**\n\nI've just finalized Sections X and XI. I'll map two primary risks with mitigations and I'm designing the interactive Executive Signature panel. The user can type their name and title to sign the proposal and view the certified document seal. The proposal now covers all sections and interactive elements.\n\n\n"}}
